      Shriram is the Vice President for Programming Languages at Brown University in Providence, RI, USA. He’s not, really, but that’s what it says on his business card. At heart, he's a person of ill-repute: a <a class="link underline dark-blue hover-bg-yellow" href="https://schemers.org/">Schemer</a>, <a class="link underline dark-blue hover-bg-yellow" href="https://racket-lang.org/">Racketeer</a>, and <a class="link underline dark-blue hover-bg-yellow" href="https://www.pyret.org/">Pyreteer</a>. He believes tropical fruit are superior to all other kinds. He is terrified of success, because he may be forced to buy a suit. He is known to interrogate his audiences to ensure they’re paying attention. <strong>So, be alert. You can read email later.</strong>
